text: There once were two great imaginative innovators.  They didn't always get along, but both believed in their dreams.  One retired, the other died.  And their dream has been left in the hands of an accountant, who runs the company like an accountant would.  "Updates" instead of innovation, year after year after year.  I hope somewhere in this world there are two other young guys, working in their garage, with little funds, just a dream, who are inventing something that will inspire this world even further.  "Apple" is already 'old'.  It feels 'safe', like visiting your grandparents for Sunday dinner.  There must be today lots of Apple users who weren't even born when Steve Jobs was alive presenting his new ideas, wearing just a pair of jeans and a t-shirt - so cool.  I feel for them.  It's like those today trying to imagine what it must have been like to have been alive when the Beatles were a group, or even the Backstreet Boys were making their hits, or the Spice Girls - all from a long ago past era with only a Kardashian or a Jenner to inspire them now.

text: the NASDAQ plummeted today after the announcement by Apple. They say there was nothing revolutionary announced. Yes. No blood glucose monitoring for Apple Watch 7 and no redesign. The apple event was deliberately underwhelming. So millions of people worldwide who would‚Äôve purchased an Apple Watch perhaps for the first time for health conditions like diabetes now have no incentive for buying one. The iPad and iPadOS remain stuck in order to protect and promote Mac sales. Apple has chosen to deliberately hold back the evolution of its iPads which it sees as being solely for media consumption and entertainment and let Macs continue to do the heavy lifting even though iPads are capable of so much more if only Apple allowed it. iPhones were an S year upgrade with nothing mind blowing in terms of features. All these many months of waiting with pent up expectations just be rewarded with a gentle letdown.
